The paper deals with the problem of learning skills that can be used for model-based planning. This involves both model-based and model-free learning, which are subfields of machine learning. The paper also deals with the problem of handling high-dimensional state-spaces, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also deals with robotics and control, which are subfields of robotics and systems engineering, respectively. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely sub-categories.
